      "message": "Generally I agree with the change, with two caveats:\n\n* The scanner currently never peeks past one byte via `s.ch`; this is the first time we do so. If we want to start doing this, I think a \"peek\" method makes sense for full clarity.\n* The existing code and tests very explicitly want the existing behavior to avoid lookahead (peeking). So I wonder if @mpvl@gmail.com, the author of this code, had a good reason behind this.\n\nMy take is that peeking a small fixed number of bytes (one or two extra) is fine, so I\u0027d approve this change, but best if we double check with Marcel.",
